content:
//Scripting language: BDScript2
//Command Trigger set your prefix. My prefix is .mute
 
/*
in Slash Command Trigger enable 'Enable global slash command'
 
Command trigger: /mute
Command Description: Mute someone on the server.
 
OPTIONS:
[user]
> add a new Option for Slash Command.
> Option Name: user
> Option Description: user you want to mute.
> Option Type: User
> Option Required: true

[duration]
> add a new Option for Slash Command.
> Option Name: duration
> Option Description: how long the user will be muted.
> Option Type: Integer
> Option Minimal and maximal values: 1 min | 40320 max
> Option Required: true
> Predefined Choices: True
[duration predefined choices]
- Choice name: 1 Minute | Choice value: 1
- Choice name: 30 Minutes | Choice value: 30
- Choice name: 1 Hour | Choice value: 60
- Choice name: 5 Hours | Choice value: 500
- Choice name: 12 Hours | Choice value: 720
- Choice name: 1 Day | Choice value: 1440
- Choice name: 3 Days | Choice value: 4320
- Choice name: 7 Days | Choice value: 10080

[reason]
> add a new Option for Slash Command.
> Option Name: reason
> Option Description: reason to mute the user.
> Option Type: Text
> Option Required: true

Reply message Code:*/

$nomention
$if[$message[2;duration]<60]
  $if[$message[2;duration]==1]
    $var[tempTimeMins;$message[2;duration]]
    $var[tempTime;Minute]
  $else
    $var[tempTimeMins;$message[2;duration]]
    $var[tempTime;Minutes]
  $endif
$elseif[$message[2;duration]<1440]
  $if[$message[2;duration]==60]
    $var[tempTimeMins;$calculate[$message[2;duration]/60]]
    $var[tempTime;Hour]
  $else
    $var[tempTimeMins;$calculate[$message[2;duration]/60]]
    $var[tempTime;Hours]
  $endif
$elseif[$message[2;duration]<10081]
  $if[$message[2;duration]==1440]
    $var[tempTimeMins;$calculate[$message[2;duration]/1440]]
    $var[tempTime;Day]
  $else
    $var[tempTimeMins;$calculate[$message[2;duration]/1440]]
    $var[tempTime;Days]
  $endif
$endif
$if[$isSlash==false]
  $argsCheck[>1;❌ Please mention the user you want to mute.]
  $botTyping
  $if[$message[3]==]
    $title[🚫 USER HAS BEEN MUTATED]
    $description[The user **<@$mentioned[1]>** (` $username[$mentioned[1]] `) was mutated from the server.

**:alarm_clock: Duration:** $var[tempTimeMins] $var[tempTime]
**🆔 User ID:** ` $mentioned[1] `
**📝 Reason:** ` Not specified `]
    $color[FF0000]
    $footer[$username]
    $footerIcon[$authorAvatar]
    $thumbnail[$userAvatar[$mentioned[1]]]
    $addTimestamp
  $else
    $title[🚫 USER HAS BEEN MUTATED]
    $description[The user **<@$mentioned[1]>** (` $username[$mentioned[1]] `) was mutated from the server.

**:alarm_clock: Duration:** $var[tempTimeMins] $var[tempTime]
**🆔 User ID:** ` $mentioned[1] `
**📝 Reason:** ` $message[3] `]
    $color[FF0000]
    $footer[$username]
    $footerIcon[$authorAvatar]
    $thumbnail[$userAvatar[$mentioned[1]]]
    $addTimestamp
  $endif
  $timeout[$message[2];$mentioned[1]]
  $deletecommand
$elseif[$isSlash==true]
$try
  $reply
  $botTyping
  $if[$message[3;reason]==]
    $title[🚫 USER HAS BEEN MUTATED]
    $description[The user **<@$message[1;user]>** (` $username[$message[1;user]] `) was mutated from the server.

**:alarm_clock: Duration:** $var[tempTimeMins] $var[tempTime]
**🆔 User ID:** ` $message[1;user] `
**📝 Reason:** ` Not specified `]
    $color[FF0000]
    $footer[$username]
    $footerIcon[$authorAvatar]
    $thumbnail[$userAvatar[$message[1;user]]]
    $addTimestamp
  $else
    $title[🚫 USER HAS BEEN MUTATED]
    $description[The user **<@$message[1;user]>** (` $username[$message[1;user]] `) was mutated from the server.

**:alarm_clock: Duration:** $var[tempTimeMins] $var[tempTime]
**🆔 User ID:** ` $message[1;user] `
**📝 Reason:** ` $message[3;reason] `]
    $color[FF0000]
    $footer[$username]
    $footerIcon[$authorAvatar]
    $thumbnail[$userAvatar[$message[1;user]]]
    $addTimestamp
  $endif
  $timeout[$message[2;duration];$message[1;user]]
$catch
  $color[E74C3C]
  $title[Error Handling]
  $addField[Function:;$error[command]]
  $addField[Error:;$error[message]]
$endtry
$endif

title: [BDFD CMD] Clear Command for BDFD Slash/CMD
content:
//Scripting language: BDScript2
//Command Trigger set your prefix. My prefix is .clear

/*
in Slash Command Trigger enable 'Enable global slash command'

Command trigger: /clear
Command Description: Delete a specific number of messages from the chat.

OPTIONS:
> add a new Option for Slash Command.
> Option Name: total
> Option Description: number of messages that will be deleted.
> Option Type: Integer
> Option Minimal and maximal values: 1 min | 100 max
> Option Required: true

Reply message Code:*/

$nomention
$if[$guildID==]
  $ephemeral
  $description[# :warning: Oops..
This command can only be used on a server!]
  $color[ffff00]
$else
  $onlyBotPerms[managemessages;:x: I don't have permission to manage messages on this server!]
  $onlyPerms[managemessages;:x: You do not have permission to manage messages on this server!]
$endif
$if[$guildID!=]
  $if[$isSlash==false]
    $botTyping
    $if[$message[1]==1]
      ```ini
      [$message[1]] Message deleted!```
    $else
      ```ini
      [$message[1]] Messages deleted!```
    $endif
  $elseif[$isSlash==true]
    $botTyping
    $if[$message[total]==1]
      ```ini
      [$message[total]] Message deleted!```
    $else
      ```ini
      [$message[total]] Messages deleted!```
    $endif
  $endif
  $try
    $if[$isSlash==false]
      $deleteIn[4s]
      $clear[$sum[$message[1];1]]
      $deletecommand
    $elseif[$isSlash==true]
      $deleteIn[4s]
      $clear[$message[total]]
    $endif
  $catch
    $color[E74C3C]
    $title[Error Handling]
    $addField[Function:;$error[command]]
    $addField[Error:;$error[message]]
  $endtry
$endif

title: garuda_add_remove
content:
#!/bin/bash

# Garuda Linux Post Install Script
# Automates installing common packages on Garuda Linux after a fresh install.
# Provides reusable functions to install packages, remove packages, and log operations.
# Customize the package lists below to suit your needs.

# Ensure the script has sudo privileges
if ! sudo true; then
  echo -e "${RED}Error: Script requires sudo privileges.${NC}"
  exit 1
fi

# Colors for formatted output
RED='\033[0;31m'
GREEN='\033[0;32m'
YELLOW='\033[1;33m'
CYAN='\033[0;36m'
ORANGE='\033[0;33m'
NC='\033[0m' # No Color

# Log function
log_message() {
  echo -e "$(date '+%Y-%m-%d %H:%M:%S') - $1"
}

# Function to pause execution and wait for user confirmation
pause_execution() {
  read -r -p "Press Enter to continue..."
}

# Check if package is installed
is_package_installed() {
  installed_version=$(pacman -Q "$1" 2>/dev/null)

  log_message "Checking if $1 is installed..."
  log_message "Installed version: $installed_version"

  if [ -n "$installed_version" ]; then
    log_message "$1 (version $installed_version) already installed."
    echo -e "${GREEN}$1 (version $installed_version) already installed.${NC}"
    return 0
  else
    log_message "$1 not installed."
    echo -e "${YELLOW}$1 not installed.${NC}"
    return 1
  fi
}

# Install a package
install_package() {
  package_name="$1"

  if sudo pacman -S --noconfirm "$package_name" >/dev/null 2>&1; then
    echo "Installed $package_name successfully."
    echo -e "${GREEN}Installed $package_name successfully.${NC}"
  else
    # Check if the error is due to a 404 (Not Found) in AUR
    if grep -q "error: failed retrieving file" <<< "$?" && grep -q "from AUR" <<< "$?"; then
      echo "AUR package $package_name not found or has a 404 error."
      echo -e "${RED}AUR package $package_name not found or has a 404 error.${NC}"
      exit_with_error "Critical error: AUR package installation failed. Check for details."
    else
      echo "Failed to install $package_name."
      echo -e "${RED}Failed to install $package_name.${NC}"
      exit_with_error "Critical error: Package installation failed. Check for details."
    fi
  fi
}

# Remove a package
remove_package() {
  package_name="$1"

  if sudo pacman -Rns --noconfirm "$package_name" >/dev/null 2>&1; then
    echo "Removed $package_name successfully."
    echo -e "${GREEN}Removed $package_name successfully.${NC}"
  else
    echo "Failed to remove $package_name."
    echo -e "${RED}Failed to remove $package_name.${NC}"
    exit_with_error "Critical error: Package removal failed. Check for details."
  fi
}

# Check if command exists
check_command() {
  command -v "$1" &>/dev/null
}

# Print error message and exit
exit_with_error() {
  log_message "Error: $1"
  echo -e "${RED}$1${NC}"
  exit 1
}

log_message "--------------------------------------------------------"
log_message " Dependencies Installation"
log_message "--------------------------------------------------------"

# Check if Git, yay, and base-devel are already installed
if ! check_command git || ! check_command yay || ! pacman -Qi base-devel &> /dev/null; then
  # Git, yay, or base-devel is not installed, install them
  log_message "Installing Git, yay, and base-devel..."

  if ! sudo pacman -S --noconfirm git yay base-devel; then
    exit_with_error "Error: Failed to install Git, yay, and base-devel. Please check your internet connection and try again."
  else
    log_message "Git, yay, and base-devel have been successfully installed."
  fi
else
  log_message "Git, yay, and base-devel are already installed."
fi
log_message "Git Yat and Base-Devel Configuration Operations completed successfully."

# Install cargo-make if needed
if check_command "cargo-make"; then
  auto_install_cargo_make=false
  echo -e "${YELLOW}cargo-make already installed.${NC}"
fi

if [ "$auto_install_cargo_make" = true ]; then
  echo -e "Installing cargo-make..."
  cargo install --force cargo-make --version 0.34.0
  echo -e "${GREEN}cargo-make installed successfully.${NC}"
fi
log_message "Cargo-Make Configuration Operations completed successfully."

log_message "--------------------------------------------------------"
log_message " Installing Packages"
log_message "--------------------------------------------------------"

# Log package installation
log_message "Installing packages."

# Get the directory where the script is located
SCRIPT_FOLDER="$(cd "$(dirname "${BASH_SOURCE[0]}")" && pwd)"

# List packages to install
mapfile -t packages_to_install <"$SCRIPT_FOLDER/packages/packages_to_install.txt"

for package in "${packages_to_install[@]}"; do
  if ! is_package_installed "$package"; then
    install_package "$package"
  else
    log_message "$package is already installed."
    echo -e "${YELLOW}$package is already installed.${NC}"
  fi
done
log_message "Installation of Packages Configuration Operations completed successfully."

log_message "--------------------------------------------------------"
log_message " Install espanso from AUR using yay"
log_message "--------------------------------------------------------"

# Log espanso installation
log_message "Installing espanso from AUR."

install_espanso() {
  if ! check_command yay; then
    exit_with_error "Error: 'yay' is not installed. Please install it before running this script."
  fi

  echo -e "${CYAN}Installing espanso from AUR...${NC}"
  if yay -S --noconfirm espanso >> /dev/null 2>&1; then
    echo -e "${GREEN}Espanso installed successfully.${NC}"
  else
    echo -e "Failed to install espanso."
    exit_with_error "Error: Failed to install espanso."
  fi
}

# Call the install_espanso function to handle install
install_espanso

# Register espanso service and start espanso after install
espanso service register
espanso start
log_message "Espanso Configuration Operations completed successfully."

log_message "--------------------------------------------------------"
log_message "Install Hardcoded Fixer from AUR using yay"
log_message "--------------------------------------------------------"

# Attempt to install hardcode-fixer-git
if yay -S --noconfirm hardcode-fixer-git >> /dev/null 2>&1; then
  echo "Installation completed successfully"
else
  echo "Failed to install hardcode-fixer-git from AUR."
fi

# Respond 'q' during the installation
echo -e "q\n" | yay -S --noconfirm hardcode-fixer-git >> /dev/null 2>&1

# Check if the installation was successful
if [ $? -eq 0 ]; then
  echo "Installation completed successfully"
else
  echo "Installation completed with errors."
fi
log_message "Hardcoded Fixer Configuration Operations completed successfully."

log_message "--------------------------------------------------------"
log_message " Removing Packages"
log_message "--------------------------------------------------------"

# Get the directory where the script is located
SCRIPT_FOLDER="$(cd "$(dirname "${BASH_SOURCE[0]}")" && pwd)"

# List packages to remove
mapfile -t packages_to_remove <"$SCRIPT_FOLDER/packages/packages_to_remove.txt"

echo -e "\e[1;${ORANGE}\e[4mREMOVING PACKAGES\e[0m"
echo

for package in "${packages_to_remove[@]}"; do
  if is_package_installed "$package"; then
    remove_package "$package"
  else
    echo -e "${YELLOW}$package is not installed.${NC}"
  fi
done
log_message "Removing Packages Configuration Operations completed successfully."

log_message "--------------------------------------------------------"
log_message " Apply hblock Rules"
log_message "--------------------------------------------------------"

echo -e "${CYAN}Applying hblock rules to block ads, tracking, and malware domains..."
if sudo hblock; then
  echo -e "${GREEN}hblock rules applied successfully.${NC}"
else
  echo -e "${RED}Failed to apply hblock rules.${NC}"
  exit_with_error "Critical error: hblock rules application failed."
fi
log_message "HBlock Configuration Operations completed successfully."

log_message "--------------------------------------------------------"
log_message " Start and Enable Firewalld"
log_message "--------------------------------------------------------"

echo -e "${CYAN}Starting the firewalld service..."
sudo systemctl start firewalld

echo -e "${CYAN}Enabling the firewalld service..."
sudo systemctl enable firewalld
log_message "Start and Enable Firewalld Configuration Operations completed successfully."

log_message "--------------------------------------------------------"
log_message " Changing The Default Shell"
log_message "--------------------------------------------------------"

# Change the default shell to Fish
if chsh -s /usr/bin/fish; then
  echo -e "${GREEN}Default shell changed to Fish successfully.${NC}"
else
  echo "Failed to change the default shell to Fish."
  echo -e "${RED}Failed to change the default shell to Fish.${NC}"
  exit_with_error "Critical error: Changing the default shell to Fish failed. Check for details."
fi
log_message "Default Shell Configuration Operations completed successfully."

log_message "--------------------------------------------------------"
log_message " Profile-Sync-Daemon (PSD) Operations"
log_message "--------------------------------------------------------"

# Log masking (disabling) the PSD service
log_message "Masking (disabling) the PSD service..."
echo -e "${CYAN}Masking (disabling) the PSD service...${NC}"
if systemctl --user mask psd 2>&1; then
  echo -e "${GREEN}PSD service masked successfully.${NC}"
else
  echo -e "${RED}Failed to mask PSD service.${NC}"
  exit_with_error "Critical error: Failed to mask PSD service. Check for details."
fi

# Stop the PSD service
echo "Stopping the PSD service..."
echo -e "${CYAN}Stopping the PSD service...${NC}"
if systemctl --user stop psd 2>&1; then
  echo -e "${GREEN}PSD service stopped successfully.${NC}"
else
  echo -e "${RED}Failed to stop PSD service.${NC}"
  exit_with_error "Critical error: Failed to stop PSD service. Check for details."
fi

# Show the status of the psd (profile-sync-daemon) service
echo "Showing the status of the PSD service..."
echo -e "${CYAN}Showing the status of the PSD service...${NC}"
status_output=$(systemctl --user status psd 2>&1)

if [ $? -eq 0 ]; then
  echo -e "${GREEN}PSD service status retrieved successfully.${NC}"
  echo -e "${CYAN}${status_output}${NC}"
else
  echo -e "${RED}Failed to retrieve PSD service status.${NC}"
  echo -e "${CYAN}${status_output}${NC}"

  # Exit with an error only if the service is not masked
  if [[ ! $status_output =~ "Unit psd.service is masked" ]]; then
    exit_with_error "Critical error: Failed to retrieve PSD service status. Check for details."
  fi
fi
log_message "PSD Configuration Operations completed successfully."

log_message "--------------------------------------------------------"
log_message " SpotDL Configuration Operations"
log_message "--------------------------------------------------------"

# Log message for SpotDL
log_message "Starting SpotDL Config File Operations..."

# Specify the name of your predefined SpotDL config file (replace 'config.json' with your file name)
predefined_config_file="config.json"

# Path to the folder containing the script
SCRIPT_FOLDER="$(cd "$(dirname "${BASH_SOURCE[0]}")" && pwd)"

# Specify the directory path where you want to store the SpotDL config file
spotdl_config_dir="$HOME/.spotdl/"

# Function to copy SpotDL config file
copy_spotdl_config() {

  source_file="$1"
  destination_dir="$2"

  # Path to the config.json file within the script folder
  config_json_path="$SCRIPT_FOLDER/spotdl/$source_file"

  # Check if the source file exists
  if [ ! -f "$config_json_path" ]; then
    echo "Error: $config_json_path not found."
    exit 1
  fi

  # Create the directory if it doesn't exist
  mkdir -p "$destination_dir"

  # Copy the SpotDL config file
  echo -e "Copying $config_json_path to $destination_dir..."
  cp "$config_json_path" "$destination_dir/config.json"

  echo -e "Copied $config_json_path to $destination_dir successfully."
}

# Call the function to copy SpotDL config file
copy_spotdl_config "$predefined_config_file" "$spotdl_config_dir"
log_message "SpotDL Configuration Operations completed successfully."

  sudo mkdir -p "$config_dir"
fi

# Move or copy the folders to /root/.config/ and log the operation
for gtk_folder in "${predefined_gtk_folders[@]}"; do
  if [ -d "$gtk_folder" ]; then
    sudo rsync -a "$gtk_folder" "$config_dir"
    # Retry removing the source directory until successful
    while ! sudo rm -r "$gtk_folder"; do
      sleep 1
    done

    echo "Moved $gtk_folder to $config_dir"
  else

done

SCRIPT_FOLDER="$(dirname "${BASH_SOURCE[0]}")"

# Function to install plasmoids
install_plasmoids() {
  plasmoids_file="$SCRIPT_FOLDER/packages/install_plasmoids.txt"
  downloads_dir="$HOME/Downloads"
  plasmoids_dir="$HOME/.local/share/plasma/plasmoids"

  mkdir -p "$plasmoids_dir"

  if [ -f "$plasmoids_file" ]; then
    mapfile -t plasmoid_git_repos < "$plasmoids_file"

    for git_repo in "${plasmoid_git_repos[@]}"; do
      echo "Cloning $git_repo..."
      git clone "$git_repo" "$downloads_dir/$(basename "$git_repo" .git)"
      plasmoid_name=$(basename "$git_repo" .git)
      cp -r "$downloads_dir/$plasmoid_name" "$plasmoids_dir"
      rm -rf "${downloads_dir:?}/$plasmoid_name"
      echo "Installed $plasmoid_name successfully."
    done
  else
    echo "Error: $plasmoids_file not found."
  fi
}

install_plasmoids
echo "Plasmoid Installation Operations completed successfully."

echo "--------------------------------------------------------"
echo " Copy KDE Configuration To Root User"
echo "--------------------------------------------------------"

# Copy KDE configuration to root user
if sudo cp -r ~/.config /root/ 2>&1; then
  if sudo chown -R root:root /root/.config 2>&1; then
    echo "KDE configuration copied to root user successfully."
    
    # Set permissions for the copied directory and its contents
    sudo chmod -R 755 /root/.config
    echo "Permissions set for /root/.config."
    
  else
    echo "Failed to change ownership of copied KDE configuration to root."
    exit_with_error "Critical error: Failed to change ownership of copied KDE configuration to root."
  fi
else
  echo "Failed to copy KDE configuration to root user."
  exit_with_error "Critical error: Failed to copy KDE configuration to root user."
fi
log_message "KDE Configuration Operations completed successfully."

log_message "SCRIPT EXECUTION COMPLETE"
echo

# crop_from_center.py

def crop_center(image_a, image_b):
    width_a, height_a = image_a.size
    width_b, height_b = image_b.size

    left = (width_a - width_b) // 2
    top = (height_a - height_b) // 2
    right = left + width_b
    bottom = top + height_b

    return image_a.crop((left, top, right, bottom))

import datasets
import json
from PIL import Image


_FEATURES = datasets.Features(
    {
        "image": datasets.Image(),
        "text": datasets.Value("string"),
        "similarity": datasets.Value("float32"),
        "hash": datasets.Value("int64"),
        "punsafe": datasets.Value("float32"),
        "pwatermark": datasets.Value("float32"),
        "AESTHETIC_SCORE": datasets.Value("float32"),
        "url": datasets.Value("string"),
        "key": datasets.Value("string"),
        "width": datasets.Value("int64"),
        "height": datasets.Value("int64"),
        "ratio": datasets.Value("float32"),
        "exif": datasets.Value("string"),
        "sha256": datasets.Value("string"),
        "status": datasets.Value("string"),
        "error_message": datasets.Value("string"),
        "original_width": datasets.Value("int64"),
        "original_height": datasets.Value("int64"),
    },
)
_VERSION = datasets.Version("0.0.2")
_DEFAULT_CONFIG = datasets.BuilderConfig(name="default", version=_VERSION)
_DESCRIPTION = (
    "Sample dataset of 100 images of different ratio from "
    "[LAION Improved Aesthetics 6plus](https://huggingface.co/datasets/ChristophSchuhmann/improved_aesthetics_6plus)\n\n"
    "I need this to see whether i can train a model on images with different ratios"
)


class SampleLAIONDatasetDifferentRatio(datasets.GeneratorBasedBuilder):
    BUILDER_CONFIGS = [_DEFAULT_CONFIG]
    DEFAULT_CONFIG_NAME = "default"

    def _info(self):
        return datasets.DatasetInfo(
            description=_DESCRIPTION,
            features=_FEATURES,
        )

    def _split_generators(self, dl_manager):
        metadata_path = "/100-files.txt"
        images_dir = '/preprocessed_2256k/train'

        return [
            datasets.SplitGenerator(
                name=datasets.Split.TRAIN,
                gen_kwargs={
                    "metadata_path": metadata_path,
                    "images_dir": images_dir,
                },
            ),
        ]

    def _generate_examples(self, metadata_path, images_dir):
        with open(metadata_path) as f:
            metadata = json.load(f)

        for file_name in metadata:
            image = Image.open(f"{images_dir}/{file_name}.jpg")
            with open(f"{images_dir}/{file_name}.txt") as f:
                text = f.read()

            with open(f"{images_dir}/{file_name}.json") as f:
                data = json.load(f)
                
            to_return = {
                "image": image,
                "text": text,
                "ratio": data["width"] / data["height"],
                
                "width": data["width"],
                "height": data["height"],
                "similarity": data["similarity"],
                "hash": data["hash"],
                "punsafe": data["punsafe"],
                "pwatermark": data["pwatermark"],
                "AESTHETIC_SCORE": data["AESTHETIC_SCORE"],
                "url": data["url"],
                "key": data["key"],
                "exif": data["exif"],
                "sha256": data["sha256"],
                "status": data["status"],
                "error_message": data["error_message"],
                "original_width": data["original_width"],
                "original_height": data["original_height"],
            }

            yield file_name, to_return

current_height = 0  # текущата височина на мравката
day = 0  # брояч за деня

while current_height < 20:
    day += 1  # увеличаваме броя на деня
    current_height += 2  # мравката се изкачва с 2 метра през деня

    if current_height >= 20:
        break  # ако мравката е достигнала или надвишила 20 метра, прекратяваме цикъла

    current_height -= 1  # мравката слиза с 1 метър през нощта

print(f"Мравката ще е на 20-тия метър на {day}-тия ден.")

	local function update(input)
		local delta = input.Position - dragStart
		pcall(function()
			Main:TweenPosition(UDim2.new(startPos.X.Scale, startPos.X.Offset + delta.X, startPos.Y.Scale, startPos.Y.Offset + delta.Y),"Out","Quad",0.1,true,nil)
		end)
	end
	Main.InputBegan:Connect(function(input)
		if input.UserInputType == Enum.UserInputType.MouseButton1 or input.UserInputType == Enum.UserInputType.Touch then
			dragging = true
			dragStart = input.Position
			startPos = Main.Position
			input.Changed:Connect(function()
				if input.UserInputState == Enum.UserInputState.End then
					dragging = false
				end
			end)
		end
	end)

	Main.InputChanged:Connect(function(input)
		if input.UserInputType == Enum.UserInputType.MouseMovement or input.UserInputType == Enum.UserInputType.Touch then
			dragInput = input

		end
	end)

	InputService.InputChanged:Connect(function(input)
		if input == dragInput and dragging then

		end
	end)

					percent = math.clamp(percent, 0, 1)

function UpdateSlider(defvalue)
    local IsSliding, Dragging = false
    local RealValue = defvalue
    local value

    local function move(Pressed)
        IsSliding = true
        local pos = UDim2.new(math.clamp((Pressed.Position.X - Sliding.AbsolutePosition.X) / Sliding.AbsoluteSize.X, 0, 1), 0, 1, 0)
        local size = UDim2.new(math.clamp((Pressed.Position.X - Sliding.AbsolutePosition.X) / Sliding.AbsoluteSize.X, 0, 1), 0, 1, 0)
        Progress:TweenSize(size, "Out", "Quart", 0.2, true)
        RealValue = (((pos.X.Scale * max) / max) * (max - min) + min)
        value = (precise and string.format("%.1f", tostring(RealValue))) or (math.floor(RealValue))
        ValueLabel.Text = tostring(value)
        UserFunc(value)
    end

    Slider.InputBegan:Connect(function(Pressed)
        if Pressed.UserInputType == Enum.UserInputType.Touch or Pressed.UserInputType == Enum.UserInputType.MouseButton1 then
            Dragging = true
            IsSliding = false
            move(Pressed)
        end
    end)

    Slider.InputEnded:Connect(function(Pressed)
        if Dragging and (Pressed.UserInputType == Enum.UserInputType.Touch or Pressed.UserInputType == Enum.UserInputType.MouseButton1) then
            Dragging = false
            IsSliding = false
            move(Pressed)
        end
    end)

    game:GetService("UserInputService").InputChanged:Connect(function(Pressed)
        if Dragging and (Pressed.UserInputType == Enum.UserInputType.Touch or Pressed.UserInputType == Enum.UserInputType.MouseMovement) then
            move(Pressed)
        end
    end)

    Slider.MouseEnter:Connect(function()
        HideColor:TweenSize(UDim2.new(0, 0, 0, 0), "Out", "Sine", 0.2, true)
    end)

    Slider.MouseLeave:Connect(function()
        if not Dragging then
            HideColor:TweenSize(UDim2.new(1, 1, 1, 1), "In", "Sine", 0.2, true)
        end
    end)

    return Slider
end

--[[

	SERVER SIDE

-- Function to revive a player in the game
function Revivir_a_Jugador(source, command, objetive)
    -- Retrieve the rank information of the player who issued the command
    local rank = exports["MR2_Cuentas"]:getValue(source, 'InfoCuenta')

    -- Check if the player's rank is high enough to use the command (rank 4 or higher)
    if not (rank["Rango"] >= 4) then
        return
    end

    -- If no target player is specified, inform the command issuer about the correct syntax
    if not (objetive) then
        return outputChatBox("#9AA498[#A03535Syntaxis#9AA498] #FFFFFF/"..command.." [Usuario]", source, 0, 0, 0, true)
    end

    -- Find the target player by their name
    local objetivo = getPlayerFromName(objetive)
    -- If the target player is not found (not connected), notify the command issuer
    if not (objetivo) then
        return outputChatBox("#56c450El jugador #24C5BE"..objetive.." #56c450no esta conectado.", source, 0,0,0, true)
    end

    -- Retrieve the death state of the target player
    local Estado = exports["MR2_Cuentas"]:getValue(objetivo, 'Estado')
    -- If the target player is not dead, notify the command issuer
    if not (Estado.Muerto == true) then
        return outputChatBox("#56c450El jugador #24C5BE"..objetive.." #56c450no esta muerto.", source, 0,0,0, true)
    end
    
    -- Set the target player's death state to false (revive them)
    Estado.Muerto = false
    exports["MR2_Cuentas"]:setValue(objetivo, 'Estado', Estado)
    -- Use a custom function to handle the revival process
    exports["MR3_Muertes"]:resucitar(objetivo)

    -- Notify the revived player and the command issuer about the revival
    local staff = getAccountName(getPlayerAccount(source))
    outputChatBox("#FF7800"..staff.." #56c450te ha revivido.", objetivo, 0,0,0, true)
    outputChatBox("#56c450Reviviste a #24C5BE"..objetive.."", source, 0,0,0, true)
end

-- Register the function with the command "revivir" and "revive"
addCommandHandler("revivir", Revivir_a_Jugador)
addCommandHandler("revive", Revivir_a_Jugador)

import math

import numpy as np
import scipy as sc


def main():
    """
    This performs a basic simulation of case 2: adiabatic.

    Here is how it works:
    1. If the valve pressure is above atmospheric, remove small amout of liquid l
    2. If the valve pressure is below atmospheric, set l = l/2 and add l
    3. Repeat until the pressure difference is within some tolorance

    It's basically Newton's method but without predicting the slope.
    I know this is terribly inefficient (and produces less accurate results), but it was quick to write.

    Also, numerically solves Eq. 10
    """
    # Initial conditions:
    p_A = 101325  # Pa
    p_G = 101325 * 1.2  # Pa
    h = 10  # m
    h_l0 = 5  # m
    area = 1.35  # m^2
    rho = 1000  # kg/m^3
    g = 9.81  # m/s^2
    gamma = 1.4  # constant

    # Sim tolorance
    tol = 1 * 10 ** -9  # Pa

    # You shouldn't need to do anything below this line

    print("Initial conditions:")
    print(f"\tAtmospheric pressure = {p_A} Pa")
    print(f"\tLiquid density = {rho} kg*m^-3")
    print(f"\tTank height = {h} m")
    print(f"\tTank cross section = {area} m^2")
    print(f"\tInitial gas pressure = {p_G} Pa")
    print(f"\tInitial liquid height = {h_l0} m")
    print(f"\tGamma = {gamma}")

    class Tank:
        def __init__(self, p_atmo, p_gas, height, liquid_level, cross_section, density, grav, heat_ratio, tolorance):
            self.atmo_pressure = p_atmo
            self.gas_pressure = p_gas
            self.height = height
            self.liquid_level = liquid_level
            self.cross_section = cross_section
            self.density = density
            self.grav = grav
            self.gamma = heat_ratio
            self.tolorance = tolorance

            self.gas_level = self.height - self.liquid_level
            self.head_pressure = self.density * self.grav * self.liquid_level
            self.valve_pressure = self.head_pressure + self.gas_pressure
            self.adiabatic_constant = self.gas_pressure * ((self.gas_level * self.cross_section) ** self.gamma)
            self.step_size = self.liquid_level / 10000  # If step_size is too high the result is innacurate

            root_estimates = np.linspace(0, self.liquid_level, 5)

            def nsol_func(h_l):
                # This is Eq. 10
                A = self.atmo_pressure * ((self.height - h_l) ** self.gamma)
                B = self.density * self.grav * h_l * ((self.height - h_l) ** self.gamma)
                C = self.gas_pressure * ((self.height - self.liquid_level) ** self.gamma)
                return A - B - C

            nsol = sc.optimize.fsolve(nsol_func, root_estimates, xtol=self.tolorance)

            # Removing duplicates, but I am too lazy to remove elements that are close
            self.numeric_solutions = list(set(nsol))

        def _step(self):
            self.liquid_level = self.liquid_level - self.step_size
            self.head_pressure = self.density * self.grav * self.liquid_level
            self.gas_level = self.gas_level + self.step_size
            self.gas_pressure = self.adiabatic_constant / (self.gas_level * self.cross_section) ** self.gamma
            self.valve_pressure = self.head_pressure + self.gas_pressure

            if self.valve_pressure <= self.atmo_pressure:
                self.step_size = - self.step_size / 2
            if self.step_size < 0 and self.valve_pressure > self.atmo_pressure:
                self.step_size = - self.step_size / 2

        def sim(self):
            iterations = 0
            while math.fabs(self.step_size) > self.tolorance:
                self._step()
                iterations = iterations + 1

            print(f"Iterations: {iterations}")
            print(f"Liquid Level:             {self.liquid_level}")
            print(f"Maximum Numeric Estimate: {np.max(self.numeric_solutions)}")
            print(f"Minimum Numeric Estimate: {np.min(self.numeric_solutions)}")
            print(f"Numeric Estimates Range:  {np.max(self.numeric_solutions) - np.min(self.numeric_solutions)}")

    tank = Tank(p_A, p_G, h, h_l0, area, rho, g, gamma, tol)
    tank.sim()


if __name__ == '__main__':
    main()

import math
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt


def main():
    """
    This performs a basic simulation of case 1: isothermal.
    The simulation works by assuming the volumetric flow rate is constant and decreases until
    the pressure before the check valve is less than or equal to the atmospheric pressure.

    Also calculates the analytical solution.
    """
    # Initial conditions:
    p_A = 101325  # Pa
    rho = 1000  # kg/m^3
    g = 9.81  # m/s^2
    h = 10  # m
    p_G = 101325 * 1.2  # Pa
    h_l0 = 5  # m

    # You shouldn't need to do anything below this line

    print("Initial conditions:")
    print(f"\tAtmospheric pressure = {p_A} Pa")
    print(f"\tLiquid density = {rho} kg*m^-3")
    print(f"\tTank height = {h} m")
    print(f"\tInitial gas pressure = {p_G} Pa")
    print(f"\tInitial liquid height = {h_l0} m")

    # Sim properties
    do_hist = False  # It makes a borning linear plot since I didn't code any fanciness into the sim
    h_step = 1 * 10 ** -6  # m, this is the height of the liquid subtracted per iteration
    stabilized = False
    h_l = h_l0
    p_B = rho * g * h_l + p_G
    h_hist = [h_l]

    # Expected final liquid height:
    a = rho * g
    b = -p_A - (rho * g * h)
    c = (h * (p_A - p_G)) + (p_G * h_l0)
    h_min = (-b - math.sqrt(b ** 2 - (4 * a * c))) / (2 * a)
    h_max = (-b + math.sqrt(b ** 2 - (4 * a * c))) / (2 * a)
    solution = -1
    if h_l0 > h_min > 0:
        solution = h_min
    if h_l0 > h_max > 0:
        if solution == h_min:
            raise Exception(f"Multiple valid solutions found:{h_min}, {h_max}")
        solution = h_max

    iterations = 0
    while not stabilized:
        iterations = iterations + 1

        # Exit condition
        if p_B <= p_A:
            stabilized = True

        # Updates gas pressure
        p_G = p_G * (h - h_l) / (h - h_l + h_step)

        # Subtracts some liquid. This is done after the gas pressure step becauce I
        # need the pressure before and after the liquid subtraction and this order was easier
        h_l = h_l - h_step
        if do_hist:
            h_hist = h_hist + [h_l]

        # Updates bottom pressure
        p_B = rho * g * h_l + p_G

    print(f"Iterations: {iterations}")
    print(f"Expected height:\n\t{solution}\nSimulated height:\n\t{h_l}")

    # Plotting
    if do_hist:
        x_points = list(range(len(h_hist)))
        expected_y_points = [solution] * len(h_hist)

        plt.plot(x_points, h_hist)
        plt.plot(x_points, expected_y_points)

        plt.show()


if __name__ == '__main__':
    main()

title: screensaver
content:
local monitor = peripheral.find("monitor")
term.clear()
monitor.setTextScale(0.5)
local termWidth, termHeight = term.getSize()
local speed = 1
local x = 10
local y = 10
local oldX = x
local oldY = y
local dirX = 1 
local dirY = 1

while true do
    term.clear()
    
    if x >= termWidth and dirX == 1 then
        dirX = 0
    elseif x <= 0 and dirX == 0 then  -- Corrected syntax for elseif
        dirX = 1
    end

    if y >= termHeight and dirY == 1 then  -- Corrected termWidth to termHeight
        dirY = 0
    elseif y <= 0 and dirY == 0 then
        dirY = 1
    end

    if dirX == 1 then
        x = x + speed
    else
        x = x - speed
    end

    if dirY == 1 then
        y = y + speed  -- Corrected variable name to y
    else
        y = y - speed  -- Corrected variable name to y
    end

    paintutils.drawPixel(OLDx, OLDy, colors.black)
    paintutils.drawPixel(x, y, colors.white)
    local oldX = x  -- Change to lowercase x
    local oldY = y  -- Change to lowercase y
    sleep(0.1)  -- Added a small delay to make the movement visible
end
